(43, 17, 23, 60, 5, 10, 10, NULL, 'Connection of Perfection and Strengthening', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of being made perfect and strengthened through Christ. John 17:23 speaks of being made perfect in unity, while 1 Peter 5:10 mentions being made perfect after suffering.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 23, 46, 1, 30, 30, 'I in them, and thou in me', 'Unity in Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of believers being united in Christ, as seen in both passages. John 17:23 emphasizes the unity of believers in God, while 1 Corinthians 1:30 describes being in Christ Jesus, who embodies wisdom and righteousness.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 24, 43, 17, 5, 5, NULL, 'Connection of Glory Before Creation', 'Both passages emphasize the glory that Jesus had with the Father before the world was created. This connection highlights the eternal relationship between Jesus and the Father, as well as the desire for believers to share in that glory.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 24, 43, 12, 26, 26, 'where I am', 'Connection of Presence and Service', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of being with Jesus. John 17:24 speaks of being with Him to behold His glory, while John 12:26 promises that His servants will also be where He is.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 24, 47, 4, 6, 6, 'behold my glory', 'Connection of Glory in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of glory associated with Jesus. John 17:24 speaks of beholding Christ''s glory, while 2 Corinthians 4:6 refers to the knowledge of the glory of God in the face of Jesus Christ.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 24, 1, 45, 13, 13, 'my glory', 'Connection of Glory and Presence', 'This connection highlights the theme of glory and the desire for presence. In John, Jesus expresses a wish for his followers to behold his glory, while in Genesis, Joseph desires to share his glory with his father.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 24, 62, 3, 2, 2, 'behold my glory', 'Connection of Divine Glory', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeing and being with Christ in glory. Both passages express the believers'' future experience of being with Jesus and seeing him as he is.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 24, 40, 25, 21, 21, NULL, 'Joy and Glory Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of reward and presence with the Lord. Both passages emphasize the joy and glory that come from being faithful and being with God.', 'theme', 0.384, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 24, 42, 22, 28, 30, 'behold my glory', 'Connection of Kingdom and Glory', 'This connection highlights the promise of being with Jesus and sharing in His glory, as seen in both passages. John 17:24 speaks of beholding His glory, while Luke 22:30 mentions sitting at His table in the kingdom.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 25, 43, 17, 11, 11, NULL, 'Unity and Knowledge of God', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between Jesus, the Father, and His followers. The phrase ''Holy Father'' in John 17:11 connects to the knowledge of God in John 17:25, highlighting the importance of unity and divine protection.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 25, 43, 7, 29, 29, 'I have known thee', 'Knowledge of the Father', 'Both passages emphasize the speaker''s knowledge of the Father and their divine sending. In John 17:25, the speaker acknowledges knowing the Father, while in John 7:29, the speaker asserts being sent by Him, highlighting a direct relationship.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 25, 42, 10, 22, 22, 'I have known thee', 'Knowledge of the Father and Son', 'Both passages emphasize the exclusive knowledge of the Father and the Son. John 17:25 highlights that Jesus knows the Father, while Luke 10:22 states that only the Son knows the Father, reinforcing the intimate relationship between them.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 25, 47, 4, 4, 4, 'the world hath not known thee', 'Knowledge of God and Blindness', 'This connection highlights the contrast between knowing God and being blinded to His truth. John 17:25 emphasizes the knowledge of God through Christ, while 2 Corinthians 4:4 describes how the god of this world blinds those who do not believe, preventing them from recognizing the light of the gospel.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 25, 58, 8, 11, 11, 'known thee', 'Knowledge of God', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of knowing God. John 17:25 highlights that Jesus and his followers know the Father, while Hebrews 8:11 states that all will know the Lord, indicating a universal understanding of God.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 25, 23, 45, 21, 21, 'I have known thee', 'Knowledge of God and Salvation', 'This connection highlights the theme of knowing God as presented in both passages. John emphasizes the knowledge of the Father through Jesus, while Isaiah declares the Lord as a just God and Saviour, indicating a relationship with Him.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 25, 40, 11, 27, 27, 'known thee', 'Knowledge of the Father and Son', 'This connection highlights the theme of knowledge between the Father and the Son. Both passages emphasize that true knowledge of the Father comes through the Son, indicating a unique relationship and revelation.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 26, 43, 17, 23, 23, 'I in them', 'Unity and Divine Love', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of unity among believers through the indwelling of Christ and the love of God. The phrase ''I in them'' connects the two verses, highlighting the relationship between Jesus, the Father, and the believers.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 26, 43, 17, 6, 6, 'thy name', 'Manifestation of God''s Name', 'Both passages emphasize the declaration and manifestation of God''s name to the disciples. This connection highlights the continuity of Jesus'' mission to reveal God''s love and identity to those given to Him.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 26, 62, 4, 13, 14, NULL, 'Connection of Divine Presence', 'Both passages emphasize the indwelling of God in believers. John 17:26 speaks of the love and presence of God in them, while 1 John 4:13-14 affirms that believers dwell in Him through His Spirit.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 26, 58, 2, 12, 12, NULL, 'Declaration of God''s Name', 'Both passages emphasize the act of declaring God''s name. John 17:26 speaks of declaring God''s name to the disciples, while Hebrews 2:12 mentions declaring it to the brethren in the church.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 26, 19, 22, 22, 22, 'declare it', 'Declaration of God''s Name', 'This connection highlights the theme of declaring God''s name. Both passages emphasize the act of proclaiming God''s name to others, linking the love of God with communal praise.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
